[
  {
    "text": "With the introduction of the revolutionary iPhone X ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=1"
  },
  {
    "text": "and Apple TV 4K, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=4"
  },
  {
    "text": "the video experience is taken to a whole new level ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=6"
  },
  {
    "text": "with the addition of support for high dynamic range video.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=8"
  },
  {
    "text": "With HD, you only see 16 million colors. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=13"
  },
  {
    "text": "But with HDR, you see one billion colors. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=16"
  },
  {
    "text": "HDR allows content creators ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=20"
  },
  {
    "text": "to use a much richer and vibrant color palette, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=22"
  },
  {
    "text": "which results in unbelievable and stunning image quality.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=24"
  },
  {
    "text": "To better understand how HDR works, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=30"
  },
  {
    "text": "let's first take a look ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=33"
  },
  {
    "text": "at the evolution in color capabilities. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=34"
  },
  {
    "text": "Here is a representation of the visible color spectrum. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=37"
  },
  {
    "text": "With the introduction of HD in 1990, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=40"
  },
  {
    "text": "the color space was defined in ITU Rec 709 ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=43"
  },
  {
    "text": "and covered about 36 percent of the visible spectrum. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=46"
  },
  {
    "text": "But, a lot has changed since 1990, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=51"
  },
  {
    "text": "and since then, the P3 color space was introduced. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=54"
  },
  {
    "text": "This color space is widely supported across our platforms ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=58"
  },
  {
    "text": "for all types of app content. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=61"
  },
  {
    "text": "Then in 2012, Recommendation 2020 ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=64"
  },
  {
    "text": "was introduced to define the color space ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=67"
  },
  {
    "text": "for Ultra High-Definition television, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=69"
  },
  {
    "text": "which offers a much wider color space ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=72"
  },
  {
    "text": "that covers more than 75 percent of the visible spectrum. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=74"
  },
  {
    "text": "Video content can now be delivered to supported devices ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=78"
  },
  {
    "text": "in any of these three color spaces, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=81"
  },
  {
    "text": "enabling far more realistic and rich color reproduction.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=84"
  },
  {
    "text": "But, the color space itself isn't the whole story. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=89"
  },
  {
    "text": "The luminance range and settings of the target display ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=92"
  },
  {
    "text": "is also extremely important ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=95"
  },
  {
    "text": "and impacts how a given color is going to be perceived. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=97"
  },
  {
    "text": "This combination of color space and luminance range ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=101"
  },
  {
    "text": "is often described as the color volume, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=104"
  },
  {
    "text": "with the luminance values on a logarithmic scale. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=106"
  },
  {
    "text": "With standard dynamic range content, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=110"
  },
  {
    "text": "it is assumed that displays ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=112"
  },
  {
    "text": "offer a peak luminance of 100 nits, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=113"
  },
  {
    "text": "yielding a relatively modest color volume. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=116"
  },
  {
    "text": "However, HDR formats are designed to support displays ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=120"
  },
  {
    "text": "capable of up to 10,000 nits of peak luminance, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=124"
  },
  {
    "text": "yielding a much richer color volume ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=127"
  },
  {
    "text": "for content creators to work with.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=129"
  },
  {
    "text": "To further understand the impact of luminance, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=133"
  },
  {
    "text": "let's take a look at a 100 percent red square ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=135"
  },
  {
    "text": "in the P3 color space. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=138"
  },
  {
    "text": "If the brightness setting of the display is at about 50 percent, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=141"
  },
  {
    "text": "the red square might look something like this. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=144"
  },
  {
    "text": "However, if the brightness of the display is turned up, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=148"
  },
  {
    "text": "the very same RGB value looks quite different ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=151"
  },
  {
    "text": "and more intense. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=154"
  },
  {
    "text": "Similarly, if the brightness is turned down, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=156"
  },
  {
    "text": "it looks much more dull. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=158"
  },
  {
    "text": "As you can see in this illustration, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=161"
  },
  {
    "text": "simply utilizing the RGB values without having control ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=164"
  },
  {
    "text": "or context of the luminance of the display ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=167"
  },
  {
    "text": "leads to vastly different color perception by the viewer. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=169"
  },
  {
    "text": "This also doesn't take into account ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=174"
  },
  {
    "text": "other influencing factors such as the ambient light level ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=175"
  },
  {
    "text": "or the color temperature of the ambient light. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=179"
  },
  {
    "text": "Another key goal of HDR is to help improve ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=182"
  },
  {
    "text": "consistency in playback across different displays. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=185"
  },
  {
    "text": "In SDR video, the target display is assumed to be capable ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=189"
  },
  {
    "text": "of up to approximately 100 nits of peak brightness. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=192"
  },
  {
    "text": "However, the actual capabilities of modern displays ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=196"
  },
  {
    "text": "far exceeds this value, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=199"
  },
  {
    "text": "and so each display then attempts ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=201"
  },
  {
    "text": "to interpolate the appropriate brightness levels ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=203"
  },
  {
    "text": "to match its own luminance range. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=205"
  },
  {
    "text": "This leads to all kinds of variance ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=208"
  },
  {
    "text": "in the appearance of a given video ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=210"
  },
  {
    "text": "across different displays, and in many cases, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=211"
  },
  {
    "text": "a very loose interpretation of the original artistic intent.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=214"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now that you have a basic understanding ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=220"
  },
  {
    "text": "of the key elements of color and luminance, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=222"
  },
  {
    "text": "and some of the goals of HDR, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=225"
  },
  {
    "text": "let's dig into the types of HDR video that we support. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=227"
  },
  {
    "text": "We support two HDR standards: Dolby Vision and HDR10. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=231"
  },
  {
    "text": "These two formats share some common principles, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=236"
  },
  {
    "text": "but also differ in many ways.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=238"
  },
  {
    "text": "One of the commonalities between the formats ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=242"
  },
  {
    "text": "is how the luminance values are encoded. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=244"
  },
  {
    "text": "Because the human eye is more sensitive ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=246"
  },
  {
    "text": "in dark ranges than light ranges, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=248"
  },
  {
    "text": "the luminance values are encoded on a curve, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=250"
  },
  {
    "text": "so that greater detail in darks ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=253"
  },
  {
    "text": "can be encoded using the limited bits available. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=255"
  },
  {
    "text": "In SDR, the gamma curve was relatively shallow, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=258"
  },
  {
    "text": "but this was sufficient ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=262"
  },
  {
    "text": "for the assumed peak target display luminance of 100 nits. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=263"
  },
  {
    "text": "For HDR, a new luminance encoding curve ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=267"
  },
  {
    "text": "has been introduced. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=269"
  },
  {
    "text": "Known as the Perceptual Quantizer, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=271"
  },
  {
    "text": "it can better map these perceptible luminance changes ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=273"
  },
  {
    "text": "across the broader, 10,000 nit range. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=276"
  },
  {
    "text": "This curve, described in SMPTE ST 2084, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=279"
  },
  {
    "text": "allows for even smoother gradation ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=282"
  },
  {
    "text": "of dark luminance values, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=284"
  },
  {
    "text": "yielding a far better experience for the viewer. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=286"
  },
  {
    "text": "This curve is utilized by both Dolby Vision and HDR10.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=289"
  },
  {
    "text": "In HDR10, a static set of metadata ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=295"
  },
  {
    "text": "is included in the video stream.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=298"
  },
  {
    "text": "This metadata includes information about the display ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=302"
  },
  {
    "text": "on which the content was originally mastered, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=304"
  },
  {
    "text": "such as its effective color gamut, white point, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=306"
  },
  {
    "text": "and luminance range.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=311"
  },
  {
    "text": "It also includes information about the content itself, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=315"
  },
  {
    "text": "namely the peak and average luminance levels. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=318"
  },
  {
    "text": "This metadata can then be used by the target display ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=321"
  },
  {
    "text": "to tone map the content to the output capabilities ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=324"
  },
  {
    "text": "of the display.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=327"
  },
  {
    "text": "With HDR10, the metadata is applied ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=330"
  },
  {
    "text": "to the entire length of the program. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=333"
  },
  {
    "text": "Dolby Vision gives you even more control, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=336"
  },
  {
    "text": "allowing for metadata to be conveyed dynamically ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=338"
  },
  {
    "text": "on a scene-by-scene, or even frame-by-frame basis. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=341"
  },
  {
    "text": "This way, the available luminance range of the display ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=344"
  },
  {
    "text": "can be optimized throughout a program ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=348"
  },
  {
    "text": "that might include both very dark and very bright scenes.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=350"
  },
  {
    "text": "The format also carries a much broader metadata set, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=357"
  },
  {
    "text": "further enabling the target display ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=360"
  },
  {
    "text": "to perform much more detailed tone mapping ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=362"
  },
  {
    "text": "and detail management.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=364"
  },
  {
    "text": "Finally, Dolby operates a certification program ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=369"
  },
  {
    "text": "to ensure that each Dolby Vision capable display is consistent, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=372"
  },
  {
    "text": "so content will always be displayed as intended.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=376"
  },
  {
    "text": "For more information on authoring your HDR content ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=383"
  },
  {
    "text": "for delivery to supported devices, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=385"
  },
  {
    "text": "please visit our HTTP Live Streaming developer page ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=388"
  },
  {
    "text": "at\ndeveloper.apple.com/streaming.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-502/?time=391"
  }
]